metadata.name: In Between #26
metadata.description:
In Between

Genuary is an artificially generated month of time where we build code that makes beautiful things, with 31 prompts to base your code art off. Genuary 2023 took place during the month of January 2023. Afterwards, as it happens, comes Genuary 32nd. This is an imaginary week, during which we develop one of our Genuary pieces into a 32 edition "not very long"-form generative project on fx(hash).

My Genuary 32nd project is based on Genuary 22nd: Shadows, the design of which again was based on the "art deco" pattern from day 20.

The patterns form a grid-like fence structure, dividing the space and creating an infinite cage. Light coming from the outside casts stark shadows on the floor. Several variations on halftoning techniques are used to portray tone, occasionally destroying depth perception into an abstract interplay of form.

The code of this piece has been diminished into a mere 3397 characters.

You can use the URL-parameter &m=2 as a resolution multiplier, to render images larger than your screen.

(c) 2023 by Piter Pasma. https://piterpasma.nl

metadata.name: üèÅüåà Pixel Flags  #28
metadata.description:
A #genuary32nd project.

Colourful flags waving in a noisy breeze.


This is an expansion of my #genuary2023 Day 17 "A grid inside a grid inside a grid". The idea was to create a large-scale grid made up of the colours of a grid of pixels. Add disruptions for a 3-D effect, and voila, a flag! Though, the initial color grid might be very rare to generate, after all the features I've added for this Fx(hash) party.

This month provided me with an opportunity to improve my JavaScript and p5js skills. Coming from a rather static Python background, I was pleased to discover the broad possibilities of interaction and animation with p5js. For this reason, I chose to create an interactive yet contemplative work.

/// Press "P" to open the MENU \\\

You can play around with the controls to find the waving flag that suits your mood. Maybe you can even let it float on the beats of your music by checking the "Use Micro Input" box.
You can also set the different speeds and sizes. Of course, you can also record the canvas as a Gif or Png according to your disired size or length.


****
Created using p5js, the quicksettings library and what is contained in the boilerplate-p5js from TengilLejonhjarta

metadata.name: Learning to Draw #20
metadata.description:
It's a collaboration between the computer and me. I tried to teach them to draw like a human artist, with all the imperfection that it means, and they tried to teach me to draw as a computer artist, with all the perfection that it means. The result is a cluster of approximative dots, jiggly lines and perfect bubbles, highlighted by colors carefully selected by them and me, after a long night of review, arguing and drinking red wine.

This is both of us, learning to draw.

PS: If any wanted or unwanted bug is found in an iteration, consider it as a blessing from the Genart Gods

Cheat codes:
* Press 1-8 to change resolution (or add &res=x to the url)
* Press s to save a PNG (or add &s=1 to the url)

metadata.name: Gribouillis #107
metadata.description:
"Gribouillis" tends to reproduce the result of what you could draw without too much thinking on your sketchbook; an automatic drawing while listening to a call or podcast... Or something you would draw on the napkin of a restaurant without a strong focus...
Those kind of drawing that don't have a lot of meaning, but that, sometimes, give you find some comfort.

---

This is a "screenshot" of the current researches and work I'm doing to emulate a sensation of sketching.

---

Open the link and add '#hd' in the URL to have a A3 size of the artwork.

---

Made to run in browser, especially Chrome.
Works on most recent iPhones.

---

metadata.name: Monsoon #213
metadata.description:
Optimization. It's something that haunts all programmers. Including me. But no longer! Monsoon is a study into the optimization of particle systems for the web. Looking especially deep into dynamic grids and dynamic frame rates.

As for the piece itself, it's a reference to how busy this modern world is. How we're all constantly on the go, whether that is physically, or mentally. Almost feeling like a monsoon. A storm of information. A storm of life. A storm of work. A storm of thoughts. A storm of emotions. A storm of everything. And it's all so fast.

As are the particles. They're all moving around these cyclones of information. Glowing up like neon signs in a busy city. Moving so fast it's almost a blur. Forming into something greater than the sum of its parts.

metadata.name: Haste Season #39
metadata.description:
‚ÄúDo not spoil the wonder with haste.‚Äù
‚Äï J.R.R. Tolkien, The Return of the King

This piece is here to point us to the fact that Haste season is upon us. It is the season when more people are moving than usual, and the dynamic movement of each person gives our world a wonderful composition. But it also increases the chance that something really bad will happen. Let's ensure that the chaotic image of cities, crowds, and haste that is before us becomes the perfect image of chaos. Image of people who love and respect one another. Image of wonder that we can be.

Made with P5js.
Bajiru, December 2022.

metadata.name: Geode #29
metadata.description:
A single seed shape is chosen from 13, and placed onto the plane. At every step, a copy of this seed is laid edge-to-edge adjacent to an existing shape, without causing any overlaps. This copy is colored based on the edge it shares with the existing shape. The process continues until the animation completes.

New shapes are placed closest to a moving target. In some mints, this target is slow moving, causing new shapes to expand radially from the seed. In other mints, this target races around, causing new shapes to chase it. 

Each of the 13 shapes forms different patterns under different circumstances. Not all patterns will be explored.

Controls:
  - SPACE: Pause/unpause the animation.
  - ENTER: Skip the animation.
  - R: Restart the animation.

URL Params:
  - "preview=1": Skip the animation.
  - "flex=1": Adapt the boundaries to the size of the window.
  - ‚Äúslow=1‚Äù: Draw only one shape per frame.
